hands_on_practices.solution:
Define for each phase $i$ the total mass released $M_{i} = T_{i} m_{i}$, where $T_{i}$ is the phase duration and $m_{i}$ is the annual mass released. The total ozone depletion impact over a phase is $J_{\text{ODP},i} = M_{i} \,\text{ODP}_{i} = T_{i} m_{i} \,\text{ODP}_{i}$, and the total climate impact is $J_{\text{GWP},i} = M_{i} \,\text{GWP}_{i} = T_{i} m_{i} \,\text{GWP}_{i}$. Both ODP and GWP are dimensionless; $T_{i}$ (years) times $m_{i}$ (kg/year) yields kg, so each total impact has units proportional to kg times a dimensionless index, and the requested ratios are dimensionless.

Compute the ODP ratio for Phase 2 relative to Phase 1:
$$
R_{\text{ODP}}=\frac{J_{\text{ODP},2}}{J_{\text{ODP},1}}=\frac{T_{2} m_{2} \,\text{ODP}_{2}}{T_{1} m_{1} \,\text{ODP}_{1}}
=\frac{20\cdot 135 \cdot 0.055}{11\cdot 120 \cdot 0.82}.
$$
Evaluate and simplify:
$$
\frac{20\cdot 135 \cdot 0.055}{11\cdot 120 \cdot 0.82}
=\frac{148.5}{1082.4}
=\frac{1485}{10824}
=\frac{495}{3608}
=\frac{45}{328}
\approx 0.137195\ldots
$$
Rounded to three significant figures: $R_{\text{ODP}}=0.137$.

Compute the GWP ratio for Phase 3 relative to Phase 1:
$$
R_{\text{GWP}}=\frac{J_{\text{GWP},3}}{J_{\text{GWP},1}}=\frac{T_{3} m_{3} \,\text{GWP}_{3}}{T_{1} m_{1} \,\text{GWP}_{1}}
=\frac{10\cdot 40 \cdot 1300}{11\cdot 120 \cdot 10200}.
$$
Evaluate and simplify:
$$
\frac{10\cdot 40 \cdot 1300}{11\cdot 120 \cdot 10200}
=\frac{520000}{13464000}
=\frac{520}{13464}
=\frac{65}{1683}
\approx 0.038621509\ldots
$$
Rounded to three significant figures: $R_{\text{GWP}}=0.0386$.

Therefore, the requested pair is $[R_{\text{ODP}}, R_{\text{GWP}}]=[0.137, 0.0386]$.
